Step 1: Calculate the Current Ratio using the end‐balance sheet values:
 • Total Current Assets = 14,619,619.72 
 • Total Current Liabilities = 7,605,149.91 
 • Current Ratio = 14,619,619.72 / 7,605,149.91 ≈ 1.92

Step 2: Calculate the Inventory Turnover Ratio.
• For the average inventory, since the beginning inventory was 0 and the end inventory is 8,466,430.00, the average inventory = (0 + 8,466,430.00)/2 = 4,233,215.00.
• The Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) from the income statement is 496,220.00.
• Inventory Turnover Ratio = COGS / Average Inventory = 496,220.00 / 4,233,215.00 ≈ 0.12

Thus, the solution is:
